WEBVTT

00:00.078 --> 00:01.623
<i>Previously on "Blood & Oil"... </i>

00:01.718 --> 00:04.554
Wick knows about us, which is why
he asked me to bug you for the feds.

00:04.938 --> 00:07.038
You were there at the rig fire.

00:07.073 --> 00:08.382
I've gone through the photos a dozen times.

00:08.407 --> 00:09.656
It's just a watch.

00:09.681 --> 00:11.492
That watch belonged to my grandfather.

00:11.517 --> 00:13.017
God, how could he do this?

00:13.031 --> 00:14.497
If I don't give these
people what they want,

00:14.532 --> 00:16.032
they're gonna kill my son.

00:16.067 --> 00:17.767
70 billion barrels.

00:17.802 --> 00:20.737
Located under the Black Elk reservation.

00:20.772 --> 00:22.872
So you're here to see
Chief Whitecloud, too?

00:22.907 --> 00:23.873
Great minds.

00:23.908 --> 00:25.942
It's not every day two oil companies

00:25.977 --> 00:27.377
come chasing after our mineral rights.

00:27.412 --> 00:29.545
♪

00:29.581 --> 00:30.680
Alex: If you were my wife,

00:30.715 --> 00:32.115
the only use I'd have for another woman

00:32.150 --> 00:33.683
would be to tell her how amazing you are.

00:33.718 --> 00:34.717
Thank you, Alex.

00:34.742 --> 00:36.730
- I'm pregnant.
- What?

00:36.755 --> 00:38.855
And I don't know if it's Hap's or Wick's.

00:41.026 --> 00:44.527
<i>♪ I got 99 people ♪</i>

00:44.562 --> 00:45.695
[Sighs]

00:45.730 --> 00:47.964
<i>♪ Tell me 99 things ♪</i>

00:47.999 --> 00:50.833
<i>♪ I got 99 reasons ♪</i>

00:50.869 --> 00:52.302
Good morning, Hap.

00:52.764 --> 00:54.470
It's a beautiful day, isn't it?

00:54.506 --> 00:58.537
Annie, any day I close a $1 trillion deal,

00:58.568 --> 01:00.043
it's a beautiful day.

01:00.756 --> 01:02.312
Chief Whitecloud called you here, too?

01:02.347 --> 01:03.546
Well, yeah.

01:03.811 --> 01:07.483
Only to sign the largest
oil deal in American history.

01:07.818 --> 01:09.018
Oh, here she comes.

01:09.054 --> 01:10.887
So be graceful in defeat.

01:10.922 --> 01:12.088
It is Christmas.

01:12.123 --> 01:13.323
♪

01:13.358 --> 01:14.424
Hi.

01:14.928 --> 01:16.903
- Annie.
- Hi, Elaine.

01:16.928 --> 01:17.732
Hap.

01:18.263 --> 01:19.529
Sorry for the short notice.

01:19.782 --> 01:22.116
I wanted you both to hear this from me.

01:23.686 --> 01:25.335
We're not going with either of you.

01:26.107 --> 01:27.003
What?

01:27.967 --> 01:30.239
You're not taking any outside bids?

01:30.490 --> 01:31.818
We're not saying no.

01:32.310 --> 01:34.326
We just need to explore all of our options.

01:35.615 --> 01:37.209
Thanks for your understanding.

01:37.949 --> 01:40.683
<i>[Music continues]</i>

01:40.719 --> 01:46.356
And thank you, Annie Briggs,
for costing me $1 trillion.

01:46.391 --> 01:48.803
I'll have my accountant send you the bill.

01:50.829 --> 01:52.028
[Sighs]

01:52.063 --> 01:55.698
♪

01:57.000 --> 02:03.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:14.048 --> 02:15.451
You're sure this was Hap's cup?

02:15.487 --> 02:17.079
Positive.

02:23.054 --> 02:25.790
It's about time I got some answers, eh?

02:31.735 --> 02:36.478
-- Synced and corrected by ChrisKe --
-- www.addic7ed.com --

02:38.143 --> 02:40.176
[Chatter]

02:40.688 --> 02:42.478
Cody: Relax, Jules.

02:42.514 --> 02:44.384
As long as the baby's healthy,

02:44.409 --> 02:46.493
everything else will work itself out.

02:46.999 --> 02:48.732
I promise.

02:48.886 --> 02:49.851
Right.

02:49.876 --> 02:51.942
Sorry to keep you waiting.

02:55.360 --> 02:56.692
Cody.

02:56.728 --> 02:58.261
- Hi.
- Hi.

02:58.296 --> 02:59.762
Nice... this is a nice
surprise. How are you?

02:59.798 --> 03:00.688
I'm good.

03:00.713 --> 03:02.852
Sorry to interrupt this little reunion,

03:02.877 --> 03:04.310
- but if we could...
- Right.

03:04.335 --> 03:05.968
Of course.

03:05.993 --> 03:07.110
Sorry.

03:13.243 --> 03:14.677
I have good news, Jules.

03:14.712 --> 03:16.227
You have a perfectly healthy baby.

03:16.252 --> 03:17.252
[Chuckles]

03:19.092 --> 03:20.191
[Exhales sharply]

03:21.196 --> 03:23.119
And the paternity result?

03:23.501 --> 03:24.754
The lab ran some tests

03:24.789 --> 03:26.938
on the DNA samples you
brought in for both men.

03:27.317 --> 03:28.950
So when you're ready...

03:29.297 --> 03:30.993
Here are the preliminary results.

03:31.596 --> 03:35.731
♪

03:35.756 --> 03:38.023
Excuse me, I need a moment.

03:40.755 --> 03:42.021
[Door opens]

03:42.046 --> 03:46.315
♪

03:47.993 --> 03:49.645
Thank you for everything.

03:49.931 --> 03:52.055
I don't know what she'd do without you.

03:54.155 --> 03:55.743
You know I'm here for both of you.

03:56.020 --> 03:57.520
♪

03:58.063 --> 03:59.462
I'm gonna go find Jules.

04:00.792 --> 04:02.425
[Door closes]

04:03.040 --> 04:05.165
Come on.
Let's get you home.

04:08.379 --> 04:11.480
♪

04:14.321 --> 04:15.905
Excuse me.

04:15.940 --> 04:19.563
I'd like the medical file on
a patient named Jules Jackman.

04:19.878 --> 04:24.046
♪

04:24.696 --> 04:26.883
Brigitte, I want garland
hung from every mantel.

04:26.918 --> 04:30.386
The house needs to be ready for
the family party tomorrow night.

04:30.421 --> 04:31.446
[Cellphone rings]

04:31.471 --> 04:32.871
Excuse me.

04:33.024 --> 04:34.490
[Cellphone beeps]

04:37.196 --> 04:39.495
I told you not to call
unless you had something.

04:39.798 --> 04:42.532
Well, I definitely have something for you.

04:43.220 --> 04:45.033
Check your in-box, Mrs. Briggs.

04:48.567 --> 04:53.403
[Footsteps]

04:54.345 --> 04:55.745
Cody.

04:55.780 --> 04:57.713
[Sighs]

04:57.756 --> 05:01.609
Sorry, I just came to get some of my stuff.

05:01.781 --> 05:03.837
You shouldn't be moving out.
You should be coming home.

05:04.079 --> 05:05.715
Don't you think it'd
be a little crowded here

05:05.751 --> 05:06.783
with your girlfriend?

05:07.298 --> 05:08.664
My girlfriend?

05:09.024 --> 05:10.099
Emma.

05:10.134 --> 05:12.868
The one you were kissing
last night at the Tack Room.

05:12.893 --> 05:13.980
Cody...

05:14.431 --> 05:15.730
No, no, no, Cody, listen.

05:15.765 --> 05:17.064
I... we were drinking.

05:17.100 --> 05:19.233
I was pissed off, okay, and she...

05:19.269 --> 05:21.335
<i>I mean, she kissed me, you know.</i>

05:21.371 --> 05:22.503
[Scoffs]

05:22.539 --> 05:23.938
I know that sounds ridiculous.

05:23.973 --> 05:25.573
I mean, I saw you go off with Alex.

05:25.608 --> 05:27.945
- I didn't know what to think.
- Well, we're friends.

05:27.970 --> 05:29.377
And unlike you, I don't need

05:29.446 --> 05:32.563
to fall into the arms of someone
else to make myself feel better.

05:33.016 --> 05:35.116
♪

05:35.151 --> 05:36.352
[Sighs]

05:37.923 --> 05:39.787
How did we get here?

05:40.174 --> 05:41.251
I don't know.

05:42.868 --> 05:44.392
I think it's this place.

05:44.427 --> 05:45.827
[Sighs]

05:47.329 --> 05:49.497
It takes everything that's
good and turns it bad, you know?

05:50.501 --> 05:53.836
Every deal becomes some
opportunity to use someone,

05:53.861 --> 05:56.685
and every opportunity becomes another
chance to screw someone over.

05:56.710 --> 05:59.811
♪

06:03.508 --> 06:05.313
You know, sometimes, I just...

06:06.064 --> 06:07.702
Think I was happier in Florida.

06:08.577 --> 06:09.509
[Scoffs]

06:09.876 --> 06:11.233
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:12.524 --> 06:15.078
Even with the yellow
flies and hurricane season?

06:15.103 --> 06:18.170
[Laughs]

06:18.681 --> 06:19.813
The truth is,

06:19.849 --> 06:21.712
I'd give anything to go
back to that version of me.

06:22.776 --> 06:23.930
Of us.

06:24.920 --> 06:26.386
♪

06:27.125 --> 06:28.422
Then...

06:29.617 --> 06:30.976
Why don't we?

06:31.494 --> 06:33.494
♪

06:34.026 --> 06:36.289
I'm willing to take another chance on you.

06:38.625 --> 06:39.561
On us.

06:39.586 --> 06:42.536
♪

06:42.914 --> 06:44.615
Look, if that's not what you want,

06:44.640 --> 06:46.674
then you just... You
really got to be honest now.

06:46.699 --> 06:47.765
No, I do.

06:48.106 --> 06:50.038
It is what I want.
I just...

06:50.711 --> 06:51.977
♪

06:53.098 --> 06:55.131
I got to tie up some loose ends.

06:55.156 --> 06:56.468
Okay.

06:57.662 --> 06:59.395
♪

07:00.711 --> 07:02.101
Tomorrow's Christmas Eve.

07:02.126 --> 07:03.726
I'll be at the Tack Room at midnight,

07:03.751 --> 07:05.601
bags packed, car loaded.

07:06.071 --> 07:08.093
If you're not there,
I'm leaving without you.

07:10.320 --> 07:14.156
It's now or never, because
I'm not looking back.

07:14.191 --> 07:17.392
♪

07:20.964 --> 07:23.598
[Sighs]

07:27.249 --> 07:28.835
[Beeps]

07:30.541 --> 07:31.706
Hey, Lace.

07:31.742 --> 07:32.828
Hi, Dad.

07:32.891 --> 07:36.647
Well, that was a hell of a morning 
on the reservation deal, wasn't it?

07:37.140 --> 07:38.280
Yeah.

07:39.220 --> 07:41.491
You're not here to talk
about the deal, are you?

07:42.545 --> 07:44.512
I have to tell you something, Dad.

07:47.633 --> 07:49.093
You okay, kid?

07:49.935 --> 07:51.132
I know that look.

07:51.157 --> 07:52.672
It doesn't mean good news.

07:53.430 --> 07:55.179
Dad, um...

07:56.149 --> 07:58.950
I'm sorry to interrupt,
but something's happened.

07:59.313 --> 08:00.512
What's up, A.J.?

08:00.547 --> 08:02.013
It's the Saudis.

08:02.523 --> 08:04.549
I think they killed my son.

08:04.585 --> 08:07.619
♪

08:10.461 --> 08:11.842
<i>I miss you, Dad.</i>

08:11.867 --> 08:13.600
<i>A.J.: I miss you, too, Khalid.</i>

08:14.007 --> 08:14.939
<i>I love you.</i>

08:14.964 --> 08:16.563
<i>I love you, too, daddy.</i>

08:16.588 --> 08:17.854
<i>[Shouting in Arabic]</i>

08:17.879 --> 08:19.846
<i>[Whistle blows]</i>

08:19.871 --> 08:21.137
<i>[Screaming]</i>

08:21.162 --> 08:23.262
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

08:23.437 --> 08:24.903
♪

08:26.133 --> 08:27.432
[Sighs]

08:27.468 --> 08:28.914
That was 30 minutes ago.

08:28.939 --> 08:30.039
Then the link went dead.

08:30.671 --> 08:33.164
I mean, they must know I'm
working for you... otherwise...

08:33.188 --> 08:34.855
A.J., you don't know anything for sure yet.

08:34.880 --> 08:36.312
♪

08:36.813 --> 08:39.380
Play that back, just the last part.

08:40.714 --> 08:42.246
[Cellphone beeps]

08:42.283 --> 08:44.416
<i>I love you, too, daddy.</i>

08:44.451 --> 08:46.118
<i>[Shouting in Arabic]</i>

08:46.153 --> 08:47.920
<i>[Whistle blows] There.</i>

08:47.955 --> 08:49.468
<i>[Screaming] I know that sound.</i>

08:49.493 --> 08:51.192
That's the shift-change whistle.

08:51.460 --> 08:52.793
Out at one of the rigs.

08:52.818 --> 08:55.039
They don't blow whistles
at the rigs in Saudi Arabia.

08:55.064 --> 08:58.465
<i>Your son isn't in Saudi Arabia,
because that's one of my rigs.</i>

08:58.976 --> 09:00.699
Right here in Rock Springs.

09:00.976 --> 09:03.898
And if he's here, we're gonna find him.

09:03.923 --> 09:06.157
Zager, get me security.

09:06.346 --> 09:08.380
Loop in the sheriff.

09:08.405 --> 09:10.872
♪

09:18.773 --> 09:20.547
[Knock on door]

09:28.461 --> 09:30.361
Carla, hey.

09:30.386 --> 09:31.617
May I come in?

09:31.969 --> 09:34.103
Sure. I-i guess.

09:35.492 --> 09:38.453
You're looking surprisingly
well, considering.

09:39.628 --> 09:42.250
All right, Carla, I'm not in
the mood for your games today.

09:42.275 --> 09:43.781
So if you don't mind, I've got work to do.

09:44.140 --> 09:45.726
You're a lot of things, Jules,

09:45.751 --> 09:48.137
but I would have never
pegged you as unoriginal.

09:49.990 --> 09:52.490
Getting knocked up just to keep your man?

09:52.581 --> 09:53.947
A little trite, isn't it?

09:54.044 --> 09:55.844
How the hell do you know about that?

09:55.869 --> 09:56.968
The question is,

09:56.993 --> 09:59.360
does my husband know he's
gonna father another child?

10:00.242 --> 10:02.716
I'm assuming you're not here
to help plan the baby shower.

10:03.351 --> 10:04.929
<i>Jules: So what are you here for, Carla?</i>

10:04.954 --> 10:05.919
To threaten me?

10:05.955 --> 10:07.254
To make you an offer.

10:08.524 --> 10:11.392
I will pay you 50% over
market value for the Tack Room.

10:11.427 --> 10:12.593
[Laughs]

10:12.628 --> 10:15.262
And provide a generous
allowance for you and your child

10:15.297 --> 10:16.997
for the rest of your lives.

10:17.033 --> 10:21.303
In exchange, you move away,
you never speak to Hap again,

10:21.328 --> 10:23.929
and you never tell him about your baby.

10:24.937 --> 10:26.865
So you want to buy me, right?

10:26.901 --> 10:27.901
Is that it?

10:27.935 --> 10:29.434
Come on, Carla.

10:29.470 --> 10:30.736
What makes you think

10:30.771 --> 10:32.437
I would even consider
taking a penny of your money?

10:33.000 --> 10:35.574
Because you betrayed Hap,
and he hates you for it.

10:36.422 --> 10:38.141
And when he finds out about the baby,

10:38.177 --> 10:40.210
he'll sue you for custody and he'll win.

10:40.245 --> 10:43.429
Chances are, you will
never see your child again.

10:44.000 --> 10:45.549
Think about my offer, Jules.

10:45.584 --> 10:47.351
You won't get a better one.

10:47.386 --> 10:49.753
♪

10:51.195 --> 10:52.161
Thank you.

10:52.196 --> 10:53.054
[Cellphone beeps]

10:53.079 --> 10:54.879
You were right, Hap.

10:54.906 --> 10:56.973
Audio forensics just confirmed the match.

10:57.008 --> 10:59.442
Mr. Menendez, your
recording matches the whistle

10:59.477 --> 11:02.234
that's right here on the eastern
side of Briggs Oil company.

11:02.347 --> 11:03.780
How long before you find that boy?

11:04.586 --> 11:05.593
I don't know.

11:05.618 --> 11:08.175
We checked every home
within earshot of that rig.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.033
Right now we're onto this area right here,

11:10.058 --> 11:11.357
which is the last quadrant.

11:11.393 --> 11:13.626
Man: Alpha team leader to
Sheriff Hamilton, come in.

11:13.662 --> 11:14.694
Excuse me.

11:15.500 --> 11:17.257
Sergeant.

11:18.033 --> 11:20.166
We're at 122 River Walk.

11:20.202 --> 11:21.734
Lights and TV are on inside.

11:21.770 --> 11:23.269
No one's answering the door.

11:23.305 --> 11:24.471
Okay, back off.

11:24.506 --> 11:26.639
Maintain surveillance. I'm on my way.

11:26.675 --> 11:28.575
What... y-you think my son is there?

11:28.610 --> 11:30.743
Well, we're about to find out.

11:30.779 --> 11:31.984
Why don't you come along?

11:32.009 --> 11:33.141
I'll call you guys.

11:33.315 --> 11:35.949
♪

11:35.984 --> 11:39.585
- Hey. I, um, I brought this for the kids. 
- Oh, nice.

11:39.610 --> 11:40.937
- I guess I'll just leave them here? 
- Nurse: That's fine.

11:40.962 --> 11:41.928
Alex: Cody.

11:41.953 --> 11:43.820
Hi. You didn't have to do this.

11:43.845 --> 11:45.687
Oh, I remember you saying

11:45.712 --> 11:48.546
the kids in your clinic
didn't have a lot of toys,

11:48.571 --> 11:49.704
and it's Christmas.

11:49.729 --> 11:51.250
Every kid should get to open a present.

11:51.275 --> 11:53.385
Well, thank you. That's
very thoughtful of you.

11:53.410 --> 11:54.343
Sure.

11:54.378 --> 11:55.410
I-I'm glad you're here.

11:55.446 --> 11:56.511
I wanted to tell you

11:56.547 --> 11:58.113
that I'm going to be
going away for a while.

11:58.593 --> 12:00.148
Really? Why?

12:00.184 --> 12:01.617
A friend of mine called.

12:01.652 --> 12:03.507
He's with Doctors Without Borders.

12:03.669 --> 12:06.036
They're short staffed for the holidays.

12:06.455 --> 12:07.554
In Haiti.

12:09.289 --> 12:10.125
Wow.

12:10.468 --> 12:11.560
I'm going to help my mother

12:11.595 --> 12:13.859
get everything in order
here first with the oil deal.

12:14.356 --> 12:15.655
But when I spoke to him,

12:16.226 --> 12:17.966
he said they could use a
good pharmacist on the team.

12:18.002 --> 12:19.002
[Chuckles]

12:19.036 --> 12:20.736
I... I can't, Alex.

12:20.771 --> 12:23.171
I actually... I'm leaving, too.

12:23.240 --> 12:24.940
♪

12:25.991 --> 12:29.680
Billy agreed to leave Rock Springs 
and go home.

12:30.484 --> 12:32.382
Well, you must have been very persuasive.

12:34.898 --> 12:37.968
I think Billy finally realized
there's more to life than oil.

12:38.555 --> 12:39.988
Well, it's a big loss.

12:40.367 --> 12:42.591
There aren't many women
like you in this town.

12:43.875 --> 12:45.093
Thank you.

12:45.953 --> 12:47.629
[Sighs]

12:47.664 --> 12:50.098
♪

12:50.938 --> 12:52.773
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

12:54.371 --> 13:01.009
♪

13:01.914 --> 13:03.345
<i>Moving into position.</i>

13:04.679 --> 13:07.393
♪

13:07.906 --> 13:08.871
Go.

13:08.907 --> 13:10.006
♪

13:10.041 --> 13:11.173
Open door on the left!

13:11.209 --> 13:12.608
Staircase, right!

13:12.644 --> 13:13.743
Room, clear.

13:13.778 --> 13:15.177
Clear.

13:15.213 --> 13:17.780
- Clear. 
- Entering back room.

13:17.815 --> 13:19.382
♪

13:20.289 --> 13:21.817
Suspect!

13:22.477 --> 13:23.776
Stand up slowly.

13:23.819 --> 13:25.619
Turn around. Face me.

13:25.655 --> 13:26.987
Drop the weapon.

13:27.023 --> 13:28.856
Turn around. Face me.

13:28.891 --> 13:29.797
♪

13:29.822 --> 13:31.689
Drop the weapon.

13:33.162 --> 13:35.462
Echo. Suspect dead.

13:35.498 --> 13:37.965
- Repeat... suspect is dead. 
- A.J.: It's Van Ness!

13:38.000 --> 13:40.608
Sh-she's Saudi intelligence!
She's the one that has my son!

13:40.633 --> 13:42.233
A.J., wait!

13:42.268 --> 13:43.301
Khalid!

13:43.336 --> 13:44.402
Khalid!

13:44.437 --> 13:46.370
- Whoa. 
- My son!

13:46.406 --> 13:47.471
- Easy. 
- Did you find my son?

13:47.507 --> 13:48.507
We haven't found your son.

13:48.541 --> 13:49.807
- They killed my boy! 
- No!

13:49.842 --> 13:51.108
- Listen to me... 
- Khalid!

13:51.144 --> 13:52.577
Listen to me, listen to me.

13:52.612 --> 13:55.156
I need you to go back
to the truck, understand?

13:55.773 --> 13:57.148
[Thud] You hear that?

13:58.586 --> 13:59.656
Call again.

13:59.681 --> 14:01.714
Okay. Khalid!

14:01.739 --> 14:03.242
[Thud]

14:04.281 --> 14:05.647
Come with me.

14:05.672 --> 14:08.586
This way. Come, come, come.

14:09.753 --> 14:12.640
♪

14:12.665 --> 14:15.297
- Call him again.
- Khalid. Khalid!

14:15.322 --> 14:17.000
[Thud]

14:17.025 --> 14:19.867
Khalid, if that's you,
I need you to come out

14:19.892 --> 14:22.445
very, very slowly, Khalid.

14:25.158 --> 14:27.292
♪

14:27.317 --> 14:28.516
Daddy.

14:28.742 --> 14:29.841
Khalid!

14:29.866 --> 14:32.900
Daddy.

14:33.711 --> 14:34.776
♪

14:36.110 --> 14:38.844
[Siren wails]

14:38.879 --> 14:40.579
Man: Coming out.

14:40.614 --> 14:42.214
[Siren continues]

14:42.249 --> 14:43.448
[Police radio chatter]

14:43.484 --> 14:45.584
Right this way. We'll take care of you.

14:45.619 --> 14:48.828
[Indistinct shouting]

14:48.853 --> 14:50.812
[Vehicle door opens]

14:56.827 --> 14:58.140
[Knock on door]

14:58.172 --> 14:59.204
[Sighs]

15:02.781 --> 15:03.713
Alex.

15:03.749 --> 15:05.148
Do you have a minute?

15:05.729 --> 15:08.359
- [Sighs]
- To, uh, talk about your team's proposal.

15:10.125 --> 15:11.161
Yeah, sure.

15:11.198 --> 15:12.195
Come on in.

15:14.057 --> 15:16.935
I mean, I'm not sure
there's much to talk about.

15:16.970 --> 15:19.370
[Chuckles] You're taking outside bids.

15:19.890 --> 15:21.639
Cody and I are leaving Rock Springs.

15:22.812 --> 15:24.509
We're going home.

15:25.311 --> 15:26.868
- Wow. 
- Mm.

15:27.015 --> 15:27.879
Um...

15:29.522 --> 15:30.664
I'm sorry to hear that.

15:31.211 --> 15:32.217
[Sighs]

15:32.680 --> 15:34.580
'Cause I was quite impressed with your bid.

15:34.615 --> 15:36.582
[Chuckles] Really?

15:37.226 --> 15:38.851
Your numbers were fair,

15:38.985 --> 15:41.757
but we're mainly looking
for a partner we trust.

15:43.156 --> 15:45.414
And I can't help but think
that maybe I found that guy.

15:45.988 --> 15:48.388
Well, lucky for that guy, I guess, right?

15:48.961 --> 15:50.804
Luck has nothing to do with it.

15:51.441 --> 15:53.241
I say you earned it.

15:55.641 --> 15:56.740
Wait...

15:57.406 --> 15:58.984
What, you're gonna give
me the mineral rights?

15:59.760 --> 16:02.360
You're exactly the type of guy that we need

16:02.529 --> 16:04.962
to protect this land while it's drilled.

16:05.414 --> 16:07.412
[Sighs] Yeah, well, um...

16:07.437 --> 16:08.385
[Clears throat]

16:08.648 --> 16:11.359
I already told Cody I'm going
back to Florida with her,

16:11.450 --> 16:13.484
so I'm not gonna go back on my word again.

16:15.851 --> 16:17.627
Yeah, it's a dilemma, isn't it?

16:17.663 --> 16:18.945
Yeah.

16:20.014 --> 16:21.113
But what if...

16:22.375 --> 16:24.467
What if Emma and Wick were your eyes here?

16:24.961 --> 16:27.958
I mean, I could oversee the whole
operation from Florida. Would that work?

16:28.073 --> 16:29.239
No.

16:30.047 --> 16:33.422
I need you here, on the
ground, front and center.

16:33.724 --> 16:35.437
And you're the one that I trust.

16:37.640 --> 16:40.093
Look, I get it.
You're in a tough spot.

16:40.372 --> 16:41.571
Yeah.

16:41.596 --> 16:43.906
But if you leave, this
deal is off the table.

16:44.437 --> 16:46.070
And that's a shame.

16:46.480 --> 16:48.514
For about a trillion reasons.

16:48.651 --> 16:50.551
♪

16:50.586 --> 16:53.625
- Let me know what you decide.
- Yeah.

16:54.787 --> 17:02.787
♪

17:07.676 --> 17:09.286
So, what do I do?

17:09.318 --> 17:10.983
You tell Alex that we'll take the deal.

17:11.019 --> 17:12.486
I mean, Cody will understand.

17:12.521 --> 17:13.988
No, no, man. She won't.

17:14.012 --> 17:17.624
She'll say I haven't changed
and she'll go home without me.

17:18.529 --> 17:19.661
Emma?

17:19.685 --> 17:21.353
What do you think?

17:21.625 --> 17:23.825
I'd like you to stay.

17:23.849 --> 17:25.182
I would.

17:25.369 --> 17:26.836
<i>[Rock music playing]</i>

17:26.871 --> 17:29.349
But that would be me being selfish, so...

17:29.724 --> 17:31.423
As your friend, I'd tell
you to take your wife

17:31.448 --> 17:32.981
and drive out of here as fast as you can.

17:33.044 --> 17:35.578
Let us figure out how to salvage the deal.

17:35.613 --> 17:37.146
<i>If we can salvage the deal.</i>

17:37.181 --> 17:39.615
This is a once-in-a-lifetime
opportunity, Billy.

17:39.650 --> 17:41.717
- If Cody can't understand that...
- Emma: Don't listen to him.

17:42.466 --> 17:43.819
You'd say anything to beat your father.

17:43.989 --> 17:46.199
Don't you think he's gonna
feel a little resentful

17:46.224 --> 17:48.628
when he's going back to
Florida to open up a laundromat

17:48.653 --> 17:50.136
instead of building an empire?

17:50.161 --> 17:51.560
[Cellphone rings]

17:51.596 --> 17:54.530
<i>♪ Taught every thief all he knows ♪</i>

17:55.435 --> 17:57.569
[Sighs] Unbelievable.

17:57.604 --> 17:58.570
What is it?

17:58.864 --> 18:01.419
My mother has brought in a new partner.

18:02.377 --> 18:04.035
My father.

18:05.208 --> 18:06.374
Billy?

18:06.399 --> 18:07.778
Hey, Billy.

18:08.134 --> 18:09.367
[Door closes]

18:09.402 --> 18:10.716
You're working with him?

18:11.471 --> 18:13.471
It was a business decision.

18:13.787 --> 18:15.442
Why didn't you even ask me first?

18:15.834 --> 18:17.767
Alex came by my place today.

18:17.792 --> 18:20.005
He wants us to have the mineral rights.

18:21.599 --> 18:23.160
<i>He gave them to you, huh?</i>

18:23.185 --> 18:24.555
[Sighs] Yeah.

18:24.974 --> 18:26.924
Well, this really is cause for celebration.

18:27.404 --> 18:29.971
No, not for you. I control this one.

18:30.000 --> 18:32.528
All right, without me,
this deal is null and void.

18:32.759 --> 18:34.792
Billy, you're being unreasonable.

18:35.101 --> 18:38.068
There are huge advantages
to pooling our resources.

18:38.412 --> 18:39.511
No, no.

18:39.536 --> 18:41.313
I started to work with you to beat him,

18:41.348 --> 18:42.950
not to make him richer.

18:43.091 --> 18:44.849
You two are made for each other.

18:44.885 --> 18:46.450
This deal is dead.

18:47.287 --> 18:49.321
[Door closes]

18:50.246 --> 18:51.848
Don't you worry.

18:52.196 --> 18:56.405
It'll be a cold day in hell
before I let him ruin our deal.

18:56.430 --> 18:58.330
<i>[Muffled rock music playing]</i>

18:59.059 --> 19:00.492
I still can't believe

19:00.517 --> 19:03.575
you're actually thinking
of accepting Carla's offer.

19:04.333 --> 19:06.131
What have I got left?

19:06.167 --> 19:10.936
You're leaving and I have hurt
everyone I ever cared about.

19:10.971 --> 19:12.337
Still thinking about Wick, huh?

19:12.373 --> 19:15.674
Oh, you know, only all the time.

19:15.709 --> 19:17.142
<i>[Music continues]</i>

19:17.178 --> 19:18.210
Well...

19:18.841 --> 19:20.979
You can't let Carla run your life, Jules.

19:21.966 --> 19:24.330
So, what, I should just stick around here

19:24.365 --> 19:27.403
and tussle with Hap over our
kid for the rest of my life?

19:28.503 --> 19:29.513
No.

19:29.804 --> 19:31.497
No, I don't want that.

19:32.435 --> 19:34.540
What I want is what you've got.

19:34.919 --> 19:36.645
A man who loves me.

19:36.893 --> 19:40.728
He'd give up his whole
life just to be with me.

19:42.943 --> 19:44.708
I'm gonna miss you.

19:45.169 --> 19:46.271
Yeah.

19:47.872 --> 19:49.574
Really gonna miss you, too.

19:49.610 --> 19:51.810
<i>[Music continues]</i>

19:57.783 --> 19:58.982
[Knock on door]

19:59.798 --> 20:01.582
Hold on a second, I'm coming.

20:06.755 --> 20:07.895
What do you want?

20:08.709 --> 20:10.325
May I come in, Billy?

20:18.443 --> 20:20.309
You have a lovely home.

20:21.224 --> 20:23.457
[Scoffs] Yeah, well...

20:23.927 --> 20:25.778
It'll be on the market tomorrow.

20:25.803 --> 20:27.836
I'm sure you can make a competitive offer.

20:29.185 --> 20:31.192
You're gonna leave Rock Springs?

20:32.335 --> 20:33.239
Yeah.

20:33.913 --> 20:37.763
A man on the verge of
closing a $1 trillion deal?

20:39.057 --> 20:41.238
Pulling up stakes and going home?

20:41.400 --> 20:43.767
I decided I don't want to be here anymore.

20:46.383 --> 20:49.050
That don't sound like
the Billy LeFever I know.

20:49.352 --> 20:50.851
Yeah, well, maybe it took me coming here

20:50.887 --> 20:52.192
to realize what's important to me.

20:53.270 --> 20:54.555
Who's important.

20:55.457 --> 20:57.708
You know what I love about this town?

21:01.700 --> 21:04.441
The weather stinks and
the sushi will kill you.

21:04.466 --> 21:05.699
[Chuckles]

21:06.431 --> 21:09.232
But it has one thing to offer.

21:10.638 --> 21:12.706
It can make your dreams come true.

21:12.731 --> 21:14.041
♪

21:15.107 --> 21:18.309
That's why thousands of
people come here every day.

21:18.337 --> 21:20.739
You know what the difference
is between them and you?

21:21.488 --> 21:23.278
They're still dreaming.

21:24.622 --> 21:25.895
Yeah, well...

21:27.239 --> 21:29.313
Dreams change.

21:29.473 --> 21:31.506
I don't think so.

21:34.320 --> 21:35.619
I'm gonna tell you something

21:35.654 --> 21:38.575
that you're probably not
gonna want to hear, but, uh...

21:39.450 --> 21:41.458
We're not so different, you and me.

21:41.894 --> 21:44.145
I saw that right from the start.

21:46.131 --> 21:48.981
You came into town like I once did,

21:49.997 --> 21:52.446
too damn brash and too stupid

21:52.471 --> 21:55.239
to even consider failure as an option.

21:55.274 --> 21:57.040
[Scoffs]

21:58.497 --> 22:00.302
What we had was a dream.

22:02.364 --> 22:04.815
Do you know what happens
when you abandon your dreams?

22:06.138 --> 22:08.661
They don't dry up and blow away.

22:09.341 --> 22:11.716
They lodge in your gut

22:12.880 --> 22:16.356
and they gnaw at you
until there's nothing left.

22:17.372 --> 22:21.255
Except the memory of what
you once wanted to be.

22:22.247 --> 22:23.591
I made a promise to Cody.

22:24.528 --> 22:25.826
Cody will understand.

22:26.318 --> 22:28.950
In fact, if she really loves you,

22:29.567 --> 22:31.886
she'll be right there by your side.

22:32.127 --> 22:33.896
And then you know what?

22:34.090 --> 22:36.622
You really will be like me, Billy.

22:38.628 --> 22:41.129
You'll have it all.

22:41.164 --> 22:42.930
♪

22:44.685 --> 22:46.700
And let there be light.

22:47.208 --> 22:49.108
[Laughs]

22:49.143 --> 22:51.949
You do love playing God, Hap Briggs.

22:51.974 --> 22:54.933
A role that some think that I was born for.

22:54.958 --> 22:56.491
Merry Christmas, partner.

22:56.526 --> 22:57.592
Merry Christmas.

22:57.628 --> 22:59.794
[Chuckles]

22:59.830 --> 23:00.599
Wick.

23:00.624 --> 23:02.231
Carla: Merry Christmas.

23:02.771 --> 23:04.435
Anyone else need a drink?

23:04.476 --> 23:05.989
Yes, thank you.

23:07.037 --> 23:08.970
Carla: I heard we're all joining forces.

23:09.014 --> 23:11.014
Yes, all for the greater good.

23:11.041 --> 23:13.108
Speaking of which, has Billy shown up yet?

23:13.143 --> 23:16.411
Chief Whitecloud is sending
over contracts for Black Elk.

23:16.446 --> 23:18.380
If he doesn't show up to sign,

23:18.415 --> 23:20.782
our alliance is over before it begins.

23:20.817 --> 23:21.850
[Chuckles]

23:22.091 --> 23:24.426
If I know my boy Billy, he'll be here.

23:24.451 --> 23:25.483
Enjoy.

23:25.518 --> 23:26.984
Thank you.

23:27.020 --> 23:29.120
<i>♪ Hark, the herald angels sing ♪</i>

23:29.155 --> 23:30.054
<i>♪ glory to the newborn king ♪</i>

23:30.090 --> 23:31.222
[Sighs]

23:31.771 --> 23:34.739
Well, I'm glad you decided
to be the bigger man

23:34.774 --> 23:36.007
and come tonight.

23:36.042 --> 23:38.263
After everything that he's done to us,

23:38.951 --> 23:40.884
how can you just let it go?

23:40.919 --> 23:42.552
Pretend like nothing ever happened.

23:42.939 --> 23:45.072
That's what families do.

23:45.114 --> 23:47.381
They forgive and move on.

23:48.481 --> 23:50.894
<i>♪ Hark, the herald angels sing ♪</i>

23:50.919 --> 23:52.295
Hap: Billy!

23:52.331 --> 23:53.927
♪

23:53.952 --> 23:56.419
- I'm glad you made it.
- Sir.

23:56.444 --> 23:58.511
Well, I've been thinking
a lot about what you said,

23:58.674 --> 24:00.074
and, um, you're right.

24:00.266 --> 24:01.465
I want it all.

24:01.540 --> 24:02.806
[Chuckles]

24:05.110 --> 24:07.444
I wanted to come and tell you personally.

24:09.170 --> 24:10.836
Right, yeah. Um...

24:11.365 --> 24:12.761
And you're sure about this?

24:12.795 --> 24:13.928
Yes.

24:13.963 --> 24:15.930
The technician at the lab
said it's highly unusual,

24:15.965 --> 24:17.064
but it does happen.

24:18.864 --> 24:20.591
Thank you, Dr. White.

24:21.825 --> 24:23.427
I want you to call me if you need anything.

24:24.073 --> 24:27.207
♪

24:30.005 --> 24:31.538
[Door opens]

24:31.563 --> 24:34.731
[Indistinct conversations,
glasses clinking]

24:38.935 --> 24:40.668
- Alex: Hey. 
- Mm, hi.

24:41.068 --> 24:43.567
- Thanks for giving us a moment.
- No problem.

24:44.639 --> 24:46.806
You know, before you go...

24:46.974 --> 24:48.872
<i>[Rock music playing]</i>

24:49.903 --> 24:51.497
I want to give this to you.

24:54.677 --> 24:57.153
- A plane ticket.
- Round trip to Haiti,

24:57.178 --> 24:59.111
in case you change your mind about coming.

24:59.154 --> 25:00.220
[Chuckles]

25:00.255 --> 25:02.722
Or if things with Billy don't work out.

25:02.758 --> 25:05.058
<i>[Music continues]</i>

25:12.634 --> 25:15.068
<i>["Deck the halls" playing]</i>

25:15.103 --> 25:18.572
[Indistinct conversation]

25:18.607 --> 25:21.741
<i>[Music continues]</i>

25:27.395 --> 25:30.517
There was a part of me that
hoped you'd come to your senses

25:30.552 --> 25:32.652
and were long gone with Cody by now.

25:32.688 --> 25:34.020
Yeah, well...

25:35.333 --> 25:37.222
How am I supposed to walk
away from something like this?

25:37.247 --> 25:39.605
<i>[Music continues]</i>

25:39.630 --> 25:41.697
After I sign the contracts,
I'll explain to her

25:41.732 --> 25:43.499
that a deal like this makes it possible

25:43.534 --> 25:46.035
for us to take care of
our families forever.

25:46.482 --> 25:48.582
It's not just my dream... It's our dream.

25:48.781 --> 25:49.980
Be careful.

25:51.310 --> 25:54.054
Sometimes the guys that want
it all end up with nothing.

25:54.090 --> 25:56.223
<i>[Music continues]</i>

25:56.258 --> 25:57.324
[Chuckles]

25:58.552 --> 26:01.121
Turned out to be a pretty nice Christmas.

26:01.157 --> 26:02.591
Yes, it did.

26:02.701 --> 26:03.901
Come here.

26:04.093 --> 26:06.560
<i>[Music continues]</i>

26:10.091 --> 26:11.606
You look beautiful.

26:12.059 --> 26:13.450
Thanks, Dad.

26:13.724 --> 26:14.964
You don't look too bad yourself.

26:14.992 --> 26:16.892
[Laughs] Yeah.

26:18.567 --> 26:22.237
Hey, uh, when you came
into my office yesterday,

26:22.262 --> 26:24.886
you had something to tell me. What was it?

26:26.701 --> 26:28.767
It doesn't matter right now.

26:28.803 --> 26:31.575
'Cause I got the feeling

26:31.600 --> 26:35.035
that you were gonna tell
me something about Wick.

26:35.142 --> 26:37.843
♪

26:43.764 --> 26:46.208
If something's bothering you about Wick...

26:47.521 --> 26:49.067
You got to tell me.

26:51.012 --> 26:52.364
Lacey?

26:55.763 --> 26:56.862
[Sighs]

26:57.364 --> 26:59.398
Dad...

26:59.433 --> 27:02.901
[Crying]

27:02.937 --> 27:05.938
♪

27:12.780 --> 27:15.781
[Keypad beeping]

27:39.505 --> 27:41.505
[Dialing]

27:41.541 --> 27:43.541
[Ringing]

27:43.576 --> 27:45.843
Carla: Hello?

27:45.878 --> 27:47.144
Carla, it's Jules.

27:47.180 --> 27:48.546
How are you, Jules?

27:48.581 --> 27:49.581
We should meet.

27:50.950 --> 27:52.550
All right, pop.

27:52.585 --> 27:54.885
What's so important?

27:56.289 --> 27:58.997
♪

27:59.208 --> 28:03.292
You know, as a parent,
you're never really sure

28:03.317 --> 28:05.958
that you're doing the
right thing for your kids.

28:06.755 --> 28:11.778
But sometimes, it becomes
abundantly clear...

28:14.247 --> 28:16.640
When you've done them wrong.

28:16.676 --> 28:18.209
Okay, I think I know where this is going.

28:18.244 --> 28:19.020
Look...

28:19.045 --> 28:20.519
Wick, just let me finish.

28:20.546 --> 28:21.979
♪

28:22.614 --> 28:24.748
I haven't been a good father to you.

28:24.784 --> 28:27.418
Th-there's just no
other way to explain it.

28:28.864 --> 28:30.841
I'm sorry for that.

28:32.310 --> 28:34.458
But you need to explain something to me.

28:35.662 --> 28:37.106
What do you mean, explain?

28:37.131 --> 28:41.100
How could you put a gun in my face?

28:41.434 --> 28:44.661
- Dad, what are you...
- How's that feel, Wick?

28:44.686 --> 28:46.753
To be looking down the barrel of a gun

28:47.614 --> 28:51.724
and somebody that you love
is pointing it at your face.

28:52.395 --> 28:55.012
I know how that feels, don't I, Wick?

28:55.048 --> 28:57.214
♪

28:57.874 --> 28:59.692
Don't I?

29:04.982 --> 29:06.148
Yeah.

29:07.575 --> 29:10.052
You know how that feels.

29:10.087 --> 29:12.521
♪

29:13.701 --> 29:17.102
But what are you gonna do?
Are you gonna shoot me?

29:17.138 --> 29:19.205
♪

29:19.240 --> 29:21.185
[Sighs]

29:21.210 --> 29:22.552
No.

29:23.491 --> 29:25.391
♪

29:25.416 --> 29:26.567
[Gun thuds]

29:27.949 --> 29:29.782
♪

29:29.817 --> 29:34.161
You've been crying out for
my attention your whole life.

29:34.334 --> 29:35.950
I never gave it to you.

29:37.484 --> 29:39.403
Not in the way you needed.

29:42.981 --> 29:46.677
So if you pointed a gun at my face,

29:47.583 --> 29:49.270
there's only one reason.

29:50.599 --> 29:52.200
I pushed you into it.

29:52.707 --> 29:55.708
♪

29:57.224 --> 29:59.645
Forgive me, Wick.

29:59.680 --> 30:03.349
So that I can forgive you.

30:04.122 --> 30:06.173
[Voice breaking] And we can move forward.

30:06.232 --> 30:10.334
♪

30:12.294 --> 30:14.361
[Voice breaking] Yeah, I forgive you.

30:14.397 --> 30:18.465
♪

30:22.813 --> 30:26.181
Lacey: I bet you and Khalid
are happy to be going back home.

30:26.919 --> 30:29.294
We talked about it, and, um...

30:29.393 --> 30:31.794
And we decided we're already home.

30:35.122 --> 30:39.421
What I'm trying to say is, Khalid and I
would love to stay here in Rock Springs.

30:41.520 --> 30:43.691
But what about your wife?

30:43.726 --> 30:44.726
Ex-wife.

30:45.560 --> 30:47.331
As soon as the papers come through.

30:47.356 --> 30:49.459
She knows Khalid's best life is here.

30:49.919 --> 30:51.302
And so is mine.

30:52.043 --> 30:53.470
[Inhales deeply]

30:53.499 --> 30:56.385
Well, good. I'm glad.

30:56.410 --> 31:00.645
♪

31:03.380 --> 31:04.939
[Chuckles] Come here.

31:04.964 --> 31:06.830
[Chuckles]

31:06.897 --> 31:10.265
♪

31:14.294 --> 31:15.994
I'm gonna put Khalid to bed.

31:16.019 --> 31:17.519
Okay.

31:17.554 --> 31:18.820
♪

31:18.856 --> 31:20.922
You know what, he left his blanket outside.

31:21.466 --> 31:22.325
Oh...

31:22.350 --> 31:23.505
I'll go get it for you.

31:23.530 --> 31:25.075
Thank you.

31:32.661 --> 31:34.583
Your money will be in by midnight.

31:35.475 --> 31:38.509
And a stipend will be deposited
monthly into your bank account.

31:39.161 --> 31:42.075
Well, I guess it worked out for
the both of us in the end, eh?

31:43.086 --> 31:45.317
You will never have to see me again.

31:46.821 --> 31:49.044
And Hap will never know about the baby.

31:52.513 --> 31:54.577
Best of luck to you, Jules.

31:54.913 --> 31:56.313
♪

31:57.537 --> 32:00.772
You know, I can see why
he's attracted to you.

32:00.799 --> 32:02.365
♪

32:02.401 --> 32:04.734
You sure know how to close a deal.

32:04.770 --> 32:09.039
♪

32:16.981 --> 32:18.515
Billy.

32:18.550 --> 32:21.013
[Chuckles]

32:21.263 --> 32:22.829
Carla: [Chuckles] So it's official.

32:23.021 --> 32:24.354
Yep, sure is.

32:24.389 --> 32:27.924
We are the proud owners of
the Black Elk mineral rights

32:27.960 --> 32:30.160
and all that beautiful oil
that comes with it. [Chuckles]

32:30.195 --> 32:32.429
[Cellphone rings]

32:33.080 --> 32:34.974
Oh, I got to take this.
Excuse me one second.

32:34.999 --> 32:35.825
[Cellphone beeps]

32:35.850 --> 32:37.599
Thanks for getting back to me.

32:41.711 --> 32:45.446
Yes, it is. Let's have some champagne.

32:46.516 --> 32:50.117
So, this is the moment where you run off

32:50.153 --> 32:52.294
and convince the girl that
she can have it all, right?

32:53.050 --> 32:54.856
[Sighs]

32:54.917 --> 32:56.372
Yeah.

32:58.130 --> 32:59.660
Good luck, Billy.

32:59.696 --> 33:01.162
Thanks, Emma.

33:01.197 --> 33:02.897
♪

33:06.005 --> 33:07.349
Bye.

33:08.705 --> 33:12.273
♪

33:23.778 --> 33:25.841
There you are.

33:27.523 --> 33:29.290
- [Screams] 
- Don't move.

33:29.332 --> 33:30.431
Just listen.

33:31.279 --> 33:32.945
I want the USGS report.

33:33.536 --> 33:35.981
Not the doctored one you
tried to fool us with.

33:36.017 --> 33:37.616
♪

33:37.652 --> 33:39.385
[Muffled screaming]

33:39.420 --> 33:44.090
♪

33:44.727 --> 33:45.993
[Muffled scream]

33:47.755 --> 33:49.272
Help!

33:49.297 --> 33:51.297
♪

33:51.332 --> 33:52.431
Help!

33:52.467 --> 33:54.867
[Grunts]

33:54.902 --> 33:56.268
♪

33:56.304 --> 33:58.003
Billy!

33:58.039 --> 34:00.606
♪

34:00.641 --> 34:02.333
No!

34:02.944 --> 34:06.212
♪

34:08.483 --> 34:09.514
[Gun cocks]

34:09.550 --> 34:10.550
♪

34:10.914 --> 34:12.213
[Gunshot]

34:12.237 --> 34:15.639
♪

34:18.513 --> 34:22.277
I don't even want to imagine what would
have happened if you hadn't showed up.

34:22.373 --> 34:24.473
Well, I did show up.

34:25.043 --> 34:26.507
It's the end, Hap.

34:26.543 --> 34:28.877
That Saudi here will lead the feds

34:28.946 --> 34:31.074
to whatever's left of his organization.

34:31.380 --> 34:33.481
♪

34:33.505 --> 34:34.841
Thank you, buddy.

34:36.005 --> 34:37.252
Appreciate you.

34:37.288 --> 34:38.652
Take care of yourself.

34:38.775 --> 34:39.806
Oh, uh...

34:41.505 --> 34:43.158
Merry Christmas. [Chuckles]

34:43.194 --> 34:44.659
[Chuckles] Yeah.

34:45.505 --> 34:46.833
Merry Christmas, Hap.

34:46.859 --> 34:47.958
See you.

34:47.983 --> 34:49.282
All right.

34:53.864 --> 34:55.971
[Sighs]

34:56.216 --> 34:57.940
Thank God you're all right.

34:58.623 --> 35:00.022
You are all right, aren't you?

35:00.178 --> 35:01.594
I'm fine. [Sighs]

35:02.591 --> 35:05.763
- Thank God Tip and Billy were there.
- Yeah.

35:06.412 --> 35:07.945
How's he doing?

35:07.981 --> 35:08.880
Oh, groggy.

35:08.915 --> 35:10.715
He's starting to wake up.

35:10.750 --> 35:12.016
[Groans]

35:13.036 --> 35:15.286
Hey, take it... Take it easy.

35:15.321 --> 35:16.777
[Billy groans] Hey, hey, hey.

35:16.802 --> 35:19.090
Go slow, son. Go slow.

35:19.115 --> 35:20.497
You took quite a whack.

35:20.522 --> 35:22.872
No, I know. [Groans]

35:23.686 --> 35:25.177
What time is it?

35:25.275 --> 35:26.541
It's a little after midnight.

35:26.566 --> 35:28.065
Oh, no, no, no, no.

35:28.090 --> 35:29.590
I'm late. I'm late.

35:30.092 --> 35:31.325
For what?

35:31.350 --> 35:33.638
I was supposed to meet Cody
at the Tack Room at midnight.

35:33.882 --> 35:35.715
Oh, come on, please pick up, pick up.

35:37.998 --> 35:40.599
[Cellphone rings]

35:40.634 --> 35:44.970
♪

35:44.995 --> 35:46.542
[Scoffs]

35:46.567 --> 35:49.388
No more excuses, Billy.

35:52.547 --> 35:56.315
♪

36:09.278 --> 36:10.434
[Scoffs]

36:10.732 --> 36:12.031
Damn it.

36:12.066 --> 36:14.020
Billy, what is so urgent?

36:14.045 --> 36:16.245
Cody... She's leaving Rock Springs

36:16.270 --> 36:18.138
with or without me tonight, okay?

36:18.163 --> 36:20.731
I was hoping to convince her to stay,

36:20.756 --> 36:23.583
but she's probably halfway
to the interstate by now.

36:23.621 --> 36:25.691
I got a hunch if you leave right now,

36:25.716 --> 36:27.880
you'll be able to catch her
before she gets to the interstate.

36:27.915 --> 36:33.147
You don't get it, okay? If I can't
change her mind about leaving, I...

36:33.268 --> 36:36.469
♪

36:40.435 --> 36:42.052
Without Cody...

36:43.700 --> 36:45.802
What good is all this?

36:46.667 --> 36:48.300
♪

36:49.325 --> 36:51.804
If Cody's leaving town,
I'm going with her, Hap.

36:53.255 --> 36:55.403
When I go, the deal's going with me.

36:55.536 --> 36:56.736
I'm sorry.

36:57.452 --> 36:58.989
Well...

37:00.162 --> 37:01.328
[Sighs]

37:01.363 --> 37:03.747
That's not quite true.

37:03.989 --> 37:06.400
Chief Whitecloud called me back today,

37:06.435 --> 37:09.203
and apparently, her son
was using the oil deal

37:09.238 --> 37:11.438
to try and break up your marriage.

37:11.755 --> 37:13.373
Alex was playing me?

37:13.409 --> 37:16.310
The Chief was fairly horrified by this,

37:17.575 --> 37:20.314
and she agreed to give us
the deal, no strings attached.

37:21.356 --> 37:22.783
So it's yours?

37:23.396 --> 37:24.529
No.

37:24.989 --> 37:26.697
It's ours.

37:26.733 --> 37:28.433
♪

37:28.468 --> 37:31.817
And you'll be a part of
it, no matter where you are.

37:32.005 --> 37:35.273
♪

37:35.308 --> 37:37.275
Hap, I don't... I don't know what to say.

37:37.310 --> 37:38.876
You don't have to say anything.

37:39.662 --> 37:41.695
Let's just go see if we can find your wife.

37:41.730 --> 37:42.930
Yeah, yeah, thank you.

37:42.965 --> 37:44.865
All right, let's get her back.

37:44.900 --> 37:47.768
♪

37:47.803 --> 37:49.102
Jules: Wick?

37:50.339 --> 37:52.684
All right, Jules, what do you want?

37:55.911 --> 37:58.178
There's something I need to tell you.

37:58.346 --> 38:01.106
And I just need you to listen, okay?

38:02.864 --> 38:04.551
I screwed everything up.

38:04.903 --> 38:06.302
I know that now.

38:06.571 --> 38:11.140
And I know I should be
ashamed to even face you.

38:11.903 --> 38:13.927
'Cause I don't deserve you.

38:14.520 --> 38:16.442
But there's someone who does.

38:18.341 --> 38:19.655
Your child.

38:20.755 --> 38:21.991
You're pregnant?

38:22.026 --> 38:23.425
Yeah.

38:23.779 --> 38:24.811
And...

38:25.888 --> 38:27.481
It's... It's mine?

38:27.516 --> 38:29.749
♪

38:31.075 --> 38:32.819
Yeah, it is.

38:33.280 --> 38:35.980
I just found out tonight that, um...

38:36.005 --> 38:39.640
♪

38:43.458 --> 38:45.025
Look, Wick, I just...

38:45.935 --> 38:47.661
I just want to get out of here, you know?

38:47.696 --> 38:49.696
I just...

38:49.731 --> 38:51.231
I want to...

38:52.766 --> 38:56.325
[Sighs]
take this baby to someplace that's good.

38:56.817 --> 38:59.117
[Sighs] Hey.

38:59.762 --> 39:02.763
♪

39:02.798 --> 39:04.677
I want to give this kid a good life, Wick.

39:04.702 --> 39:06.669
All right, I want to give...

39:07.099 --> 39:09.233
I want to give you a good life.

39:09.502 --> 39:11.702
We could start fresh. We could...

39:12.316 --> 39:13.833
Build our own family.

39:19.755 --> 39:22.115
We can go anywhere.

39:22.323 --> 39:25.390
We can do anything.

39:25.707 --> 39:27.247
Just say yes.

39:29.825 --> 39:31.992
All you've got to do is say yes.

39:32.027 --> 39:36.296
♪

39:41.145 --> 39:42.358
[Chuckles]

39:42.383 --> 39:43.716
Yes.

39:43.741 --> 39:45.941
[Laughs]

39:46.090 --> 39:49.158
[Laughs]

39:49.311 --> 39:52.913
♪

40:05.870 --> 40:07.372
I blew it.

40:08.888 --> 40:10.020
I blew it.

40:10.056 --> 40:12.466
She's probably off with
Alex somewhere, man.

40:16.747 --> 40:18.948
[Sighs]

40:20.216 --> 40:22.216
<i>Maybe you can have it all.</i>

40:22.927 --> 40:25.620
For the rest of us, life
just don't work that way.

40:25.655 --> 40:27.155
[Door opens]

40:29.685 --> 40:33.595
Well, we might be a little
more alike than you think.

40:33.630 --> 40:36.864
♪

40:37.802 --> 40:39.133
[Chuckles]

40:39.169 --> 40:40.902
♪

40:42.427 --> 40:43.938
Don't blow it, son.

40:43.974 --> 40:46.307
[Chuckles]

40:46.343 --> 40:50.278
♪

40:58.457 --> 41:00.424
I'm so sorry I'm late.

41:02.654 --> 41:04.466
What happened to your 
face? Are you okay?

41:04.491 --> 41:05.951
That's a long story, honey.

41:05.976 --> 41:07.643
But it's okay.

41:07.668 --> 41:08.934
♪

41:10.520 --> 41:11.961
Ready?

41:12.520 --> 41:14.708
For you, my whole life.

41:16.770 --> 41:18.501
I'm gonna take you home.

41:18.536 --> 41:21.571
The best idea I've heard in a long time.

41:21.606 --> 41:23.840
♪

41:36.146 --> 41:37.778
Carla: Look at all this.

41:38.950 --> 41:42.125
As far as the eye can see, it's ours.

41:42.832 --> 41:43.828
Yep.

41:44.974 --> 41:46.763
I guess you can have it all.

41:46.931 --> 41:48.330
[Chuckles]

41:49.768 --> 41:55.747
This place isn't for everybody,
but it's definitely for you and me.

41:58.374 --> 42:00.407
[Chuckles]

42:02.347 --> 42:05.348
